title: For Sale:  FN M1930 Greek Contract Mauser
postcontent: What we have for sale here is an excellent example of a FN Herstal made Mauser carbine for Greek military contract. Based on the serial number, this rifle was produced and delivered before the Greco-Italian War where most of the Greek military saw fighting. After this, it ended up in a German Arsenal when the Nazis invaded and captured Greece during the Second World War. It eventually ended up in a Czechoslovakian Arsenal after the war where the stock was replaced by a Czech Vz.24 stock. After this, it was sold to the Romanian chetniks for contract and possibly the Yugoslavs after this. The bore and barrel are mirror sharp. Should be a great shooter for whoever purchases.DO NOT BE AFRAID TO MAKE AN OFFER!

postcontent: The Savage 93R17 FXP comes ready to take into the field with a factory mounted and bore sighted 3-9 x 40mm scope, and a non-reflective matte black synthetic stock and matte finished barrel and receiver won't spook game. The Savage 93R17 is an adult-sized bolt-action rimfire rifle that provides superb accuracy and reliability. Savage's AccuTrigger enables shooters to obtain exceptional accuracy with the Savage 93R17 FXP, by allowing you to easily adjust it to your desired weight of pull for a light, crisp release with no creep. A lever mounted within the trigger body blocks the sear unless the trigger is intentionally pressed in the center, virtually minimizing the risk of accidental discharge. The 93R17 FXP bolt features dual extractors for positive extraction of spent cases, and a 5-round, detachable magazine facilitates loading and unloading the rifle. A 2-stage safety, located on the right side of the receiver, allows the action to be cycled with the safe in the on position. title: For Sale:  Bill Fuller Hawken Rifle .40 cal percussion Match
postcontent: Up for auction is a rare Harold "Bill" Fuller Hawken rifle .40 cal. For those that don't know, he was a Master Gunsmith that lived in Cooper's Landing, Alaska. He passed away in 1988. Fuller offered an invaluable skill as one of only two gunsmiths on the entire Kenai Peninsula. He made rifles, and for those who already had them, he kept them working. His exquisite work — particularly with Hawken rifle replicas — was well known nationwide, and still is today. Feel free to ask questions about the Gun no trade serious buyer only lol thanks..
